        "description": {
            "value": "<p>These special poi are made from a rare, light metal or from fire-retardant fibers and can be ignited before being wielded. Igniting a pair of fire poi is an Interact action and requires 1 pint of @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Oil (1 pint)]{Oil} for every 10 minutes the poi remain ignited.</p>\n<p>While lit, fire poi cast dim light in a 10-foot radius; in combat, they deal 1d4 bludgeoning plus 1d4 fire damage. On a critical hit with a lit fire poi, the target takes 1 @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Persistent Damage]{Persistent} fire damage. The fire can be extinguished using the Interact action.</p>\n<p>When unlit, the poi deal only the listed bludgeoning damage. Regardless of whether it is lit, the poi's 1d4 bludgeoning damage is the weapon damage dice, so <em>striking</em> runes and other effects don't affect the fire damage.</p>"
